    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-07-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-07-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="676"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d676">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Walter S. Robertson</persName> to
                        General <persName type="to">Marshall</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-07-15">15 July
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1445 [<hi rend="italic">5445?</hi>]. Service on our 5316 re Shanghai [<hi
                        rend="italic">Shantung?</hi>]. General Clement is continuing efforts to
                    schedule new conference within a week but states that he feels no conference
                    will materialize unless very positive orders are issued direct to the commanders
                    of the area for which Chen Yi is responsible that the truce be strictly observed
                    and the fighting stopped.</p>
                <pb facs="1371" n="1359" xml:id="pg_1359"/>
                <p>Marine reports are that National Govt, forces are still pushing forward in their
                    attacks along the Tsingtao–Tsinan railroad.</p>
                <p>Therefore it is recommended that action be taken to have the Generalissimo and
                    Chairman Mao Tse-tung issue orders to all commanders involved to stop fighting
                    in order that conditions under which a profitable meeting can be held may be
                    insured.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
